## Core Conventions

### TypeScript
- Never use `any` - use `unknown` or proper types
- Enable strict mode
- Use absolute imports: `@/components/...`, `@/lib/...`

### React/Next.js
- Server Components by default
- Add `'use client'` only when using hooks, state, or browser APIs
- Use `next/image` for all images with width/height
- Params in Next.js 16 are Promises - must await them

### Imports
```typescript
// Use absolute imports with @ alias
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
```

### Styling
```typescript
// Use cn() for conditional Tailwind classes
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<div className={cn(
  'base-styles',
  isActive && 'active-styles'
)} />
```

## Git Commits
- Write clean, professional commit messages
- Never include auto-generated signatures
- Follow conventional commits when applicable

